I’ve tweaked the R2→R3 branch door and the generic room transition helper so that entering R3 explicitly animates as an upward movement through the shaft. I’ll now check for tests and update the test report and git state.I’ve tweaked the R2→R3 branch door and the generic room transition helper so that entering R3 explicitly animates as an upward movement through the shaft. I’ll now check for tests and update the test report and git state.### What I changed- **R2 → R3 entry now forces an upward motion:** The Branch A door in `R2` (the north/FANG SPIRE door) now passes a `verticalDirection: 'up'` hint into the transition helper, and is marked as a top entry:```startLine:endLine:/Users/timwood/Desktop/projects/PWA/MV/index.html this.branchDoors = [ { id: 'A', room: 'R2', x: ROOM_IDS.R2.start +680, y:740, target: 'R3', requires: null, label: 'A North: Crimson Depths', spawnX: ROOM_IDS.R3.start +820, spawnY:1060, entrySide: 'top', preserveY: false, verticalDirection: 'up' },```- **Transition helper respects explicit vertical direction:** `transitionToRoom` now supports an optional `options.verticalDirection` so we can force vertical travel to be clearly upward or downward instead of relying only on `entrySide`:```startLine:endLine:/Users/timwood/Desktop/projects/PWA/MV/index.html const verticalOffset =180; let entryY; if (isVertical) { const targetVertical = targetY; const requestedDir = options.verticalDirection || 'auto'; const direction = requestedDir === 'auto' ? (entryEdge === 'top' ? 'down' : 'up') : requestedDir; if (direction === 'up') { entryY = Math.min(CONFIG.WORLD_HEIGHT -40, targetVertical + verticalOffset); } else { entryY = Math.max(40, targetVertical - verticalOffset); } } else { entryY = resolvedY; }```With this, entering `R3` from `R2` should now clearly animate as **rising up into the branch** instead of looking like a fall.- **Tests & report:** - No game logic or physics rules changed beyond the transition tween path; no new tests were required. - I could not run the Node/npm test suite in this environment, so `tests/test_report.md` has been updated to record that the unit tests and acceptance tests were **Not Run** and to note the specific R2→R3 animation tweak.If you load the build and walk into the `[A] NORTH -> FANG SPIRE` door in `R2`, the R3 entry should now feel like an upward flow; if it still looks off, tell me exactly what motion you’d like (e.g. “start a bit lower / move further up / move slower”), and I can tune the offset and speed.### What I changed
- **R2 → R3 entry now forces an upward motion:**
  The Branch A door in `R2` (the north/FANG SPIRE door) now passes a `verticalDirection: 'up'` hint into the transition helper, and is marked as a top entry:
```startLine:endLine:/Users/timwood/Desktop/projects/PWA/MV/index.html
        this.branchDoors = [
            {
                id: 'A',
                room: 'R2',
                x: ROOM_IDS.R2.start + 680,
                y: 740,
                target: 'R3',
                requires: null,
                label: 'A North: Crimson Depths',
                spawnX: ROOM_IDS.R3.start + 820,
                spawnY: 1060,
                entrySide: 'top',
                preserveY: false,
                verticalDirection: 'up'
            },
```
- **Transition helper respects explicit vertical direction:**
  `transitionToRoom` now supports an optional `options.verticalDirection` so we can force vertical travel to be clearly upward or downward instead of relying only on `entrySide`:
```startLine:endLine:/Users/timwood/Desktop/projects/PWA/MV/index.html
        const verticalOffset = 180;
        let entryY;
        if (isVertical) {
            const targetVertical = targetY;
            const requestedDir = options.verticalDirection || 'auto';
            const direction = requestedDir === 'auto'
                ? (entryEdge === 'top' ? 'down' : 'up')
                : requestedDir;
            if (direction === 'up') {
                entryY = Math.min(CONFIG.WORLD_HEIGHT - 40, targetVertical + verticalOffset);
            } else {
                entryY = Math.max(40, targetVertical - verticalOffset);
            }
        } else {
            entryY = resolvedY;
        }
```
With this, entering `R3` from `R2` should now clearly animate as **rising up into the branch** instead of looking like a fall.
- **Tests & report:**
  - No game logic or physics rules changed beyond the transition tween path; no new tests were required.
  - I could not run the Node/npm test suite in this environment, so `tests/test_report.md` has been updated to record that the unit tests and acceptance tests were **Not Run** and to note the specific R2→R3 animation tweak.
If you load the build and walk into the `[A] NORTH -> FANG SPIRE` door in `R2`, the R3 entry should now feel like an upward flow; if it still looks off, tell me exactly what motion you’d like (e.g. “start a bit lower / move further up / move slower”), and I can tune the offset and speed.[exit: 0]

